  <prompt>
    Add a new read-only tool handler `GetWorkspaceTabContentHandler : IToolHandler` in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ToolHandlers/` per FR-57. Handler reuses the existing Pillar 6b workspace state plumbing (`WorkspaceStateService.GetTabAsync` — see architecture §6.5) to return the COMPOSED widget state (sections + values), NOT raw streaming chunks. Register in DI per ADR-010 (unconditional registration; no asymmetric Tier-1.5 anti-pattern). Add a row in `scripts/Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1` `$RowFiles` hashtable for `GET-WORKSPACE-TAB-CONTENT` toolcode following the precedent from task 092 / `RECALL-SESSION-FILE`. Integration test: run `summarize-document-for-workspace` against bff-dev → ask "make the summary shorter" → agent reads tab content via `get_workspace_tab_content` → subsequent turn reflects the modified content target.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in `IToolHandler` pattern, R6 Pillar 6b workspace state plumbing, ADR-010 DI registration, and FR-57 T2 round-trip semantics.</role>

  <goal>
    `GetWorkspaceTabContentHandler` lives at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ToolHandlers/GetWorkspaceTabContentHandler.cs` implementing `IToolHandler.ExecuteChatAsync(ChatInvocationContext, AnalysisTool, CancellationToken)` per R6 Pillar 2 contract. Handler is read-only — calls `WorkspaceStateService.GetTabAsync(tabId)` and returns the COMPOSED widget state (the section-name-keyed map per FR-54), NOT raw `section_data` streaming chunks. Registered unconditionally in `AiServicesModule` (or the existing handler-registration module per ADR-010). `Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1` has a new row entry for `GET-WORKSPACE-TAB-CONTENT` mirroring the task-092 precedent (`RECALL-SESSION-FILE`). Integration test verifies end-to-end T2 round-trip: workspace tab content is reachable from a subsequent chat turn via the new handler.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Phase 5R revised scope (spec.md §"Phase 5+7 Revised Scope" FR-57). Architecture §6.5 (Workspace state read/write) and §11.1 (R6 carry-forward — `WorkspaceStateService` + Pillar 6b handlers are already built; DO NOT REBUILD). FR-57 closes the T2 memory loop: workspace output becomes AI-readable memory on subsequent turns. Existing handler `get_workspace_tab_state` (referenced in architecture §6.5 / §8 tool inventory) returns hot tab metadata; the new `get_workspace_tab_content` returns the composed widget state (sections + values). Per NFR-A1 (T2 explicit promotion), this is a read-only handler — no new state storage; pure projection over existing Pillar 6b storage.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ToolHandlers/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ToolHandlers/UpdateWorkspaceTabHandler.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Workspace/WorkspaceStateService.cs</file>
