      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Ai/Chat/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI registration via `AiServicesModule` (or existing handler-registration module); unconditional `services.AddSingleton&lt;IToolHandler, GetWorkspaceTabContentHandler&gt;()` (no `if (flag)` block — avoids Tier-1.5 anti-pattern per CLAUDE.md §10 F.1).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stays in `Services/Ai/` boundary; no CRUD-code violations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Telemetry tier-1 safe — log tabId + handler invocation; NEVER tab content. Handler is read-only — no T3/T4 promotion bypass.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement; report delta vs current baseline (~45.65 MB); expect &lt;1 MB delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture binding">[arch §11.1] T2 round-trip via `get_workspace_tab_content` reuses Pillar 6b workspace state plumbing — do NOT add new state storage.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test update obligation (CLAUDE.md §10) — add unit test for handler + integration test for round-trip; existing tests unchanged.</constraint>
  </constraints>

