  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md §6.5 (workspace state read/write) and §11.1 (R6 carry-forward — DO NOT REBUILD `WorkspaceStateService`). Confirm `GetTabAsync` returns the composed widget state we need.</step>
    <step order="2">Read existing handler `UpdateWorkspaceTabHandler.cs` (referenced in arch §6.5) as the structural precedent for `IToolHandler` impls; mirror its constructor injection + `ExecuteChatAsync` shape.</step>
    <step order="3">Read `WorkspaceStateService.GetTabAsync` signature — confirm it returns the FR-54 section-name-keyed `sections: Record&lt;string, SectionState&gt;` shape (composed widget state, NOT raw streaming chunks).</step>
    <step order="4">Author `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ToolHandlers/GetWorkspaceTabContentHandler.cs`. Implements `IToolHandler` with `ToolCode = "GET-WORKSPACE-TAB-CONTENT"`. Constructor: `IWorkspaceStateService workspaceStateService, ILogger&lt;GetWorkspaceTabContentHandler&gt; logger`. `ExecuteChatAsync` reads `tabId` from `tool.Parameters`, calls `workspaceStateService.GetTabAsync(tabId)`, projects to a tier-1-safe response shape `{ tabId, widgetType, sections: {sectionName: composedValue} }` — NO raw chunks.</step>
    <step order="5">Register in DI: add `services.AddSingleton&lt;IToolHandler, GetWorkspaceTabContentHandler&gt;()` to `AiServicesModule` (or the canonical handler-registration module). Verify unconditional registration (no `if (flag)` block — CLAUDE.md §10 F.1).</step>
    <step order="6">Author `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-get-workspace-tab-content-row.json` with `sprk_handlerclass = "GetWorkspaceTabContentHandler"`, `sprk_toolcode = "GET-WORKSPACE-TAB-CONTENT"`, `sprk_invocationcontextmask = Chat`, `sprk_parameterschema` declaring `tabId: string (required)`, `sprk_requiredcapability = null` (always-on per arch §8.2).</step>
    <step order="7">Add a row entry in `scripts/Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1` `$RowFiles` hashtable following the task-092 precedent — mirror the `RECALL-SESSION-FILE` row entry pattern (toolcode key, JSON file path value). Idempotent upsert via alternate key on `sprk_handlerclass`.</step>
    <step order="8">Add unit test `GetWorkspaceTabContentHandlerTests` in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/ToolHandlers/`: (a) valid tabId → returns composed widget state; (b) unknown tabId → empty / not-found result; (c) verifies `WorkspaceStateService.GetTabAsync` invoked once with correct tabId; (d) verifies NO raw chunks in response (tier-1 audit).</step>
    <step order="9">Add integration test `WorkspaceMemoryRoundTripTests.SummarizeThenAskShorter_AgentReadsTabContent` in `tests/integration/`. Flow: upload NDA → run `summarize-document-for-workspace` (migrated per 118R) → assert workspace tab populated → user message "make the summary shorter" → assert agent invokes `get_workspace_tab_content` (visible in tool-trace) → subsequent turn response reflects the modified content target (not just generic shortening).</step>
    <step order="10">Run `Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1` against DEV; verify the new `sprk_analysistool` row exists; restart BFF dev; verify chat agent tool registry exposes `get_workspace_tab_content`.</step>
    <step order="11">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + `dotnet test tests/`. All tests pass.</step>
    <step order="12">Measure BFF publish size; report delta vs ~45.65 MB baseline; expect &lt;1 MB delta. code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 quality gates) — verify no asymmetric registration, no T3/T4 promotion bypass, no `IServiceProvider.GetService&lt;T&gt;` in endpoint signatures.</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 118b → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 119 (Phase 5R exit gate).</step>
  </steps>

